               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 10 a7ff., and the last line of this leaf corresponds roughly to MaitrHami 2, 11 a7ff. (for the Uy. references, cf. [[Ji et al. 1998]]: 18).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 10 a16; God Brahmā is speaking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a5.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 10 a27ff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a7.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 10 b3; God Indra is speaking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a8.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 10 b8ff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b2.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 10 b17ff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b6.&lt;/b&gt; Cf. MaitrHami 2, 11 a1-3ff. &lt;i&gt;śmāśānaśräṅkāraṃ&lt;/i&gt;: two stanzas of presumably 4 x 18 (7/7/4) syllables; this metrical passage ends in the following leaf, [[YQ II.10]]: a2, where the number ‘1’ should be a mistake for ‘2’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b6.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;pkāk&lt;/i&gt;: pace [[Schmidt KT 1999b]]: 281, there is no trace of &lt;trans&gt;&lt;i&gt;_u&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/trans&gt;, i.e. &lt;trans&gt;&lt;i&gt;p_ukāk&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/trans&gt;. Compare e.g. the akṣara &lt;i&gt;ṣkā&lt;/i&gt; in the same line.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
